<br>
You may be right, but no more so than reading scripture that supports the deity of Christ.  Christians (orthodox ones anyway) who believe that Jesus is God and in the Trinity read scripture in such a way that it supports that notion, those who disagree read the scripture differently.<br>
<br>
That is why I said that we can agree to differ on interpretation, but those who charge that Purgatory is not based on the Bible are incorrect in that assumption.  We do use the Bible to support the doctrine. <p>Christians know that it is not possible to reject or ignore God without demeaning man.<br>
- John Paul II at WYD 2002<br>
